OL,3,CUkrainian mother dies in car crash
OL,4,Cafter fleeing war
OL,6,FHer hosts paid tribute to her,
OL,7,Fdescribing her as being like a
OL,8,Fdaughter to them both.
OL,10,FThey said she was a "stalwart of the
OL,11,FUkrainian community in Swansea" with a
OL,12,Fwarm and pleasant personality "that
OL,13,Fpermeated every gathering".
OL,15,FIn a statement shared by , Ms
OL,16,FMartynova's hosts, who have not been
OL,17,Fnamed, said: "Tetiana (known locally
OL,18,Fas Tania) had fled her native city,
OL,19,FKharkiv, in Ukraine due to the ongoing
OL,20,Fwar, along with her 13-year-old son,
OL,21,Fand arrived in Swansea in July 2022.
